    "body": "### Added\n\n- **`login_anthropic()` ‚ÄĒ owned-Anthropic OAuth PKCE flow (claude CLI\n  žĚėž°īžĄĪ ž†úÍĪį).** `/login anthropic` ÍįÄ ŽćĒ žĚīžÉĀ `claude /login`\n  subprocess Ž•ľ Ūėłž∂úŪēėžßÄ žēäÍ≥† GEODE ÍįÄ žßĀž†Ď PKCE redirect flow žąėŪĖČ\n  ‚ÄĒ loopback callback server (ŽěúŽć§ free port 54123-54199), PKCE\n  code_verifier/challenge žÉĚžĄĪ, `https://platform.claude.com/oauth/\n  authorize` browser open, `https://api.anthropic.com/v1/oauth/token`\n  ŪÜ†ŪĀį ÍĶźŪôė, `~/.geode/auth.toml` žĚė `providers.anthropic` section žóź\n  ž†Äžě•. multi-candidate client_id žčúŽŹĄ path (`9d1c250a-...` ŽďĪ reverse-\n  engineered) + first-success-wins. macOS/Linux/Windows Ž™®ŽĎź ŽŹôžěĎ.\n  `read_geode_anthropic_credentials` Ūó¨ŪćľÍįÄ `read_geode_openai_\n  credentials` žôÄ ŽŹôžĚľ shape žúľŽ°ú ŽįėŪôė. `claude_code_provider.\n  resolve_claude_oauth_token` / `get_claude_oauth_metadata` ÍįÄ auth.\n  toml žöįžĄ† read + macOS keychain backwards-compat fallback. ToS Tier\n  3 (impersonation) ‚ÄĒ `claude_code_provider` žĚė module docstring žĚė\n  policy notice ÍįÄ SOT. failure žčú graceful fallback (`ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`\n  Í∂Ćžě• message).\n- **`login_anthropic()` ‚ÄĒ owned-Anthropic OAuth PKCE flow (drops\n  `claude` CLI dependency).** `/login anthropic` no longer spawns\n  `claude /login`; GEODE drives the PKCE redirect flow itself ‚ÄĒ\n  loopback callback (free port 54123-54199), PKCE\n  `code_verifier`/`challenge` pair, browser open against\n  `platform.claude.com/oauth/authorize`, token exchange at\n  `api.anthropic.com/v1/oauth/token`, persist into\n  `~/.geode/auth.toml` `providers.anthropic`. Multi-candidate\n  `client_id` loop (`9d1c250a-...` first) with first-success-wins.\n  Cross-platform (macOS / Linux / Windows). `read_geode_anthropic_\n  credentials` mirrors the OpenAI helper shape.\n  `claude_code_provider.resolve_claude_oauth_token` and\n  `get_claude_oauth_metadata` now prefer the `auth.toml` source with\n  the macOS keychain kept as a backwards-compat fallback. ToS Tier 3\n  (impersonation) per `claude_code_provider` module docstring;\n  failure surfaces an `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` fallback hint.\n\n\n- **`docs/architecture/provider-login.md` ‚ÄĒ provider login flow SOT.**\n  OpenAI (device-code) žôÄ Anthropic (PKCE redirect) žĚė OAuth flow žĚė\n  ž†ēŪē© spec žč†Í∑ú. owned-credential ŪĆ®ŪĄī (auth.toml SOT + GEODE ÍįÄ žßĀž†Ď\n  OAuth client) žĚė architecture + 5-mismatch ž†ēŪē© plan + ToS Tier\n  spectrum (0-4) ž†ēžĚė. PR C3 (owned-Anthropic PKCE ÍĶ¨ŪėĄ) žĚė reference\n  SOT.\n- **`docs/architecture/provider-login.md` ‚ÄĒ provider login flow SOT.**\n  Architecture spec for the two-provider OAuth picture: OpenAI's\n  device-code flow plus Anthropic's PKCE redirect flow share an\n  owned-credential pattern (auth.toml as SOT, GEODE acts as OAuth\n  client directly). Covers the 5 mismatch points the upcoming PR C3\n  will close and pins down the ToS Tier (0-4) spectrum the choice\n  sits in.\n\n### Removed\n\n- **`/auth` žä¨Žěėžčú Ž™ÖŽ†Ļ žôĄž†Ą ž†úÍĪį + `/login source` žč†žĄ§.** `/auth` žĚė žěĒž°ī\n  surface (`add` / `remove` / `set <provider> <source>`) ÍįÄ Ž™®ŽĎź `/login`\n  žúľŽ°ú ŪĚ°žąė. `/login source <provider> <type>` žč†Í∑ú ‚ÄĒ Íłįž°ī `/auth set` žĚė\n  credential source picker. `routing.py` žĚė `/auth` CommandSpec, `dispatcher.py`\n  žĚė cmd_auth dispatch, `core/cli/__init__.py` žĚė TTY_LOCAL_COMMANDS žĚė\n  `/auth` Ž©§Ž≤Ą, `_state.py` žĚė `COMMAND_MAP` žĚė `/auth` entry + help line,\n  `commands/__init__.py` žĚė export, `core/cli/commands/auth.py` ŪĆĆžĚľ žěźž≤ī\n  Ž™®ŽĎź ž†úÍĪį. `manage_auth` LLM tool žĚÄ backwards-compat adapter Ž°ú žú†žßÄ\n  ‚ÄĒ Ūėłž∂ú žčú `manage_login` Ž°ú forward (legacy prompts ŪėłŪôė). Plan vs\n  Profile Ž∂ĄŽ¶¨ žĚė historical Í∑ľÍĪį (`PlanRegistry` vs `ProfileStore`) ŽäĒ\n  žú†žßÄŽźėŽźė, žā¨žö©žěź žßĄžěÖž†źžĚÄ `/login` Žč®žĚľ SOT.\n- **`/auth` slash command fully removed + `/login source` introduced.**\n  The remaining `/auth` surface (`add` / `remove` / `set <provider>\n  <source>`) was folded into `/login`. The new `/login source <provider>\n  <type>` is the migrated credential-source picker (was `/auth set`,\n  PR #1203). Removed: `routing.py` entry, `dispatcher.py` dispatch +\n  import, `_TTY_LOCAL_COMMANDS` membership, `_state.py` `COMMAND_MAP` +\n  help line, `commands/__init__.py` exports, and the\n  `core/cli/commands/auth.py` source file itself. The `manage_auth`\n  LLM tool is kept as a backwards-compat adapter that forwards to\n  `manage_login` so legacy prompts still work. The underlying Plan vs\n  Profile split (`PlanRegistry` vs `ProfileStore`) is unchanged ‚ÄĒ only\n  the user-facing entry point is unified."
