    "version": "0.98.0",
    "date": "2026-05-17",
    "body": "### Changed\n\n- **`/login <provider>` ‚ÄĒ provider ŽßĆ parameter Ž°ú ŽįõŽäĒ OAuth picker\n  + `/auth login` ž†úÍĪį.** Íłįž°ī `/login oauth <provider>` žĚė 2-Žč®žĖī ŪėēŪÉúÍįÄ\n  `/login openai` / `/login anthropic` (alias: `codex`, `chatgpt`,\n  `claude`, `claude-code`) žĚė Žč®žĚľ ŪÜ†ŪĀį žßĄžěÖžúľŽ°ú Žč®žąúŪôĒ. provider name\n  ŽßĆžúľŽ°ú OAuth flow ÍįÄ ž¶Čžčú ŽŹôžěĎ ‚ÄĒ picker surface ÍįÄ `/model` žĚė mirror.\n  ž§ĎŽ≥Ķ žßĄžěÖž†źžĚīŽćė `/auth login` (status display + browser login) žĚė UI +\n  ŽįĪžóĒŽďú ŽĎź helper (`_auth_login_status`, `_sync_oauth_profile_after_login`)\n  Ž™®ŽĎź ž†úÍĪį. `/auth` ŽäĒ profile management ŽßĆ (`add` / `remove` /\n  `set <provider> <source>`). Anthropic OAuth path ÍįÄ žÉąŽ°ú `_login_oauth`\n  žēąžóź ž∂ĒÍįÄŽź® ‚ÄĒ local `claude /login` subprocess Ūėłž∂ú ŪõĄ macOS keychain\n  žĚė token žĚĄ `ProfileStore` žóź sync. test 41 pass.\n- **`/login <provider>` ‚ÄĒ provider-only OAuth picker, `/auth login`\n  removed.** The legacy `/login oauth <provider>` two-word form is now\n  `/login openai` / `/login anthropic` (aliases: `codex`, `chatgpt`,\n  `claude`, `claude-code`) ‚ÄĒ a single provider token runs the OAuth\n  flow directly, mirroring the `/model` picker surface. The redundant\n  `/auth login` entry point (status display + browser handoff) and\n  its `_auth_login_status` / `_sync_oauth_profile_after_login`\n  helpers were removed from both UI and backend. `/auth` now hosts\n  only profile management (`add` / `remove` / `set <provider>\n  <source>`). The Anthropic OAuth path is now folded into\n  `_login_oauth` ‚ÄĒ it spawns `claude /login` and then syncs the\n  resulting keychain credential into `ProfileStore`. 41 tests pass.\n\n- **`/login <provider>` canonical OAuth entry point.** `/login openai`\n  now runs the Codex Plus device-code flow directly, while\n  `/login anthropic` delegates to the local Claude Code login flow and\n  syncs the resulting keychain credential into `ProfileStore`. The old\n  `/login oauth <provider>` spelling is no longer advertised by help,\n  onboarding, or tool schema.\n- **`/login <provider>`Ž•ľ OAuth Žč®žĚľ žßĄžěÖž†źžúľŽ°ú ž†ēŽ¶¨.** `/login openai`ŽäĒ\n  Codex Plus device-code flowŽ•ľ žßĀž†Ď žč§ŪĖČŪēėÍ≥†, `/login anthropic`žĚÄ Ž°úžĽ¨\n  Claude Code login flowžóź žúĄžěĄŪēú Ží§ keychain credentialžĚĄ `ProfileStore`\n  Ž°ú ŽŹôÍłįŪôĒŪē©ŽčąŽč§. Íłįž°ī `/login oauth <provider>` ŪėēŪÉúŽäĒ help, onboarding,\n  tool schemažóźžĄú ŽćĒ žĚīžÉĀ ŽÖłž∂úŪēėžßÄ žēäžäĶŽčąŽč§.\n\n### Removed\n\n- **Legacy `/auth login` UI/backend path.** `/auth` now remains only as\n  profile management (`add`, `remove`, `set`); OAuth setup lives under\n  `/login <provider>`. The legacy auth-login status/sync helpers were\n  removed from the command package export surface.\n- **Ž†ąÍĪįžčú `/auth login` UI/backend Í≤ĹŽ°ú ž†úÍĪį.** `/auth`ŽäĒ profile ÍīÄŽ¶¨\n  (`add`, `remove`, `set`)ŽßĆ ŽčīŽčĻŪēėÍ≥† OAuth žĄ§ž†ēžĚÄ `/login <provider>`ÍįÄ\n  ŽčīŽčĻŪē©ŽčąŽč§. Íłįž°ī auth-login status/sync helperŽŹĄ command package export\n  surfacežóźžĄú ž†úÍĪįŪĖąžäĶŽčąŽč§."
